### Modal Structure Requirements
All dialog-like screens must be implemented as modal pages with:

#### 1. Modal Container
- Overlay with backdrop blur
- Centered modal container
- Header with title and close button
- Content area
- Footer with action buttons

#### 2. RTL-Aware Close Button Positioning
- Position close button based on language direction
- Use CSS order property for RTL/LTR adaptation
- Maintain consistent spacing and alignment

#### 3. Modal Styling
- Fixed positioning with overlay
- Responsive sizing (max-width/height)
- Smooth animations for open/close
- Proper z-index management

### Modal Component Guidelines
- **Overlay**: Semi-transparent backdrop
- **Content**: Centered with max-width constraints
- **Header**: Title and close button
- **Body**: Scrollable content area
- **Footer**: Action buttons
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first design


### Modal Implementation Rules
- **Click outside to close** (overlay click)
- **Escape key to close** (keyboard accessibility)
- **Focus trap** within modal
- **Scroll lock** on body when modal is open
- **Close button positioning** based on language direction
- **Responsive design** for mobile devices
- **Animation** for smooth open/close transitions
- **Accessibility** with proper ARIA attributes
- **Consistent width** across all modals
- **Scrollable content** when content exceeds modal height
- **Custom scrollbar** styling for better UX